abstract: >-
  Horosa for Windows v2.6.6 beta is a local-first metaphysics workstation that aligns the
  latest Mac-side work and adds a Windows-shell hardening pass. Mac-side: a chart-math
  correction batch across the Python engine (degree-minute string parsing, equation-of-time
  table fixes plus "±HH:MM" half-hour time zones in true solar time, solar/lunar-return
  seeding and cross-0° aspect normalization, composite midpoints taking the short arc,
  besiegement orb isolation, hour-ruler flooring); a primary-directions upgrade (precise
  display windows, Vertex promissor support, per-chart time keys, year horizon raised to
  3000 with multi-revolution recurrences, wire-protocol rev v12 across four Java
  controllers); the root-cause fix for Windows issues #24/#25 (the chat send button passed
  the click event object into the send path, so messages became the literal string
  "[object Object]" — now type-guarded), plus chat advanced parameters actually taking
  effect for OpenAI-family providers, thinking-level coverage for newer reasoning models,
  and two extra report thinking tiers; the fix for Windows issue #23 (Gemini 400: sampling
  parameters moved inside generationConfig, jar rebuilt); a UI bug-sweep batch
  (white-screen guards on corrupt localStorage, dark-mode contrast, stable list keys,
  Retina canvas sharpness, report-capture serialization). Windows-shell hardening (this
  repo): interface zoom now persists across restarts (the saved zoom factor was written
  but never read back); AI-material imports skip unreadable or oversized files instead of
  aborting whole batches; diagnostics/backup exports surface write failures gracefully;
  a concurrent-restart latch prevents duplicate embedded-runtime pairs; runtime repair
  invalidates trust caches before deletion; update timers are cleared on shutdown; the
  winget manifest stamps its real release date; and the release self-check now fails
  loudly on a stale SHA256SUMS file. Builds on the v2.6.5 synastry interaction-chain
  rebuild and casting-time mounting expansion, and the v2.6.4 full-stack sidereal zodiac
  expansion (Western charts get a
  unified tropical-or-47-ayanāṃśa zodiac selector built on Swiss Ephemeris, propagated
  through the frontend, eight Java controllers, the Python chart kernel and response echo,
  and persisted storage; Western sidereal mode shows lunar mansions / Nakshatra), Indian
  astrology completion (ayanāṃśa 6→47, house systems 4→24), the four-way AI-Analysis
  synchronization with dual-chart-technique support and AI_EXPORT_SETTINGS_VERSION 23→24
  auto-migration, AI Analysis "report" generation v1, the startup-robustness pass and the
  Windows-side issue #21 fix ("本地排盘服务未就绪" now has visible health state, a rich
  error dialog, longer transparent retry, and an actionable banner). Builds further on prior planetarium
  projection refinements, the seven Western progression techniques wired into AI analysis,
  the astrocartography/ACG map, horary/electional charts, the Heluo Lishu completion, AI
  system-proxy support, the SSE service-stability fix, the global day-boundary /
  late-zi-hour model, the Ed25519-signed in-app auto-update, 数算 methods, the harmonic
  chart, clean-machine fixes, and the Windows-only NSIS installer hardening (issue #18 —
  upgrades over the top no longer fail and no longer require a manual uninstall first) — and
  AI Analysis rework, astrology modules, traditional Chinese methods, kentang/kin backend
  integrations, AI-assisted structured export, Python and Java services, and self-contained
  Windows desktop delivery into one cross-platform release line.

